  "name": "orashift_merge",
  "notes": "Oracle-Redshift fusion. Key distinguishing features: (1) the sole not-equal operator is the invented !<> token, conflicting with all siblings; (2) EXCEPT is spelled MINUS (Oracle heritage); (3) count_distinct_null=included so COUNT(DISTINCT col) counts NULLs; (4) upper-case fold with case-sensitive quoted identifiers (Oracle style); (5) 1-based arrays; (6) semicolon required. Schema-qualified function namespaces (schema::func) are expected by convention but enforced at the application layer. Conflicts with prior slots: differs from snowacle_qualify on row-limiting (LIMIT vs QUALIFY), CTE keyword (WITH vs DEFINE), null-safe-eq spelling; differs from redgres_lateral on concat (|| vs CONCAT_WS), join syntax (plain ANSI vs LATERAL-mandatory); differs from mydb2_rollup on row-limiting (LIMIT vs ROWNUM), neq operator, mod operator; differs from bigmaria_pivot on identifier quoting (double vs backtick), boolean truthiness (strict vs c_style), set-op default (distinct vs corresponding-by); differs from sqllite_flake_agg on LIKE case sensitivity (true vs false), NULLS ordering defaults, div-by-zero (error vs null).",
